A chemical foot peel mask uses acids and keratolytics to dissolve dead skin, causing the outer layer to peel off in sheets within a week.

⸻

🔬 Key Ingredients:
	•	Glycolic/Lactic Acid (10–20%) – Exfoliates dead cells
	•	Salicylic Acid (1–3%) – Penetrates deep, clears hardened skin
	•	Urea (10–20%) – Softens and breaks down thick calluses
	•	Fruit Enzymes – Mild peeling support

⸻

⏱️ How It Works:
	1.	Wear the mask for 60–90 mins
	2.	Peeling starts on Day 4–7
	3.	Smoother skin is revealed by Day 10–14

⸻

⚠️ Caution:
	•	Use only once a month
	•	Do not apply on cuts or infections
	•	Don’t moisturize until peeling is complete
